# Ability Name			Unique Key						Category of Ability		Type										Description
Rage					KEY:Barbarian ~ Rage				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.48	DESC:In battle, you fight with primal ferocity. On your turn, you can enter a rage as a bonus action. While raging, you gain the following benefits if you aren't wearing heavy armor: You have advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws. When you make a melee weapon attack using Strength, you gain a bonus to the damage roll that increases as you gain levels as a barbarian, as shown in the Rage Damage column of the Barbarian table. You have resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage. If you are able to cast spells, you can't cast them or concentrate on them while raging. Your rage lasts for 1 minute. It ends early if you are knocked unconscious or if your turn ends and you haven't attacked a hostile creature since your last turn or taken damage since then. You can also end your rage on your turn as a bonus action. Once you have raged the number of times shown for your barbarian level in the Rages column of the Barbarian table, you must finish a long rest before you can rage again.	BONUS:VAR|MeleeStrBonus|RageDamageBonus|PREVAREQ:Raging,1	TEMPBONUS:PC|VAR|Raging|1	DEFINE:Raging|0	DEFINE:RageDamageBonus|0	DEFINE:RageTimes|0		BONUS:VAR|RageTimes|1+(BarbarianLVL>2)+(BarbarianLVL>5)+(BarbarianLVL>11)+(BarbarianLVL>16)	BONUS:VAR|RageDamageBonus|2+(BarbarianLVL>8)+(BarbarianLVL>14)	
Unarmored Defense			KEY:Barbarian ~ Unarmored Defense		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.48	DESC:While you are not wearing any armor, your Armor Class equals 10 + your Dexterity modifier + your Constitution modifier. You can use a shield and still gain this benefit.
Reckless Attack			KEY:Barbarian ~ Reckless Attack		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.48	DESC:Starting at 2nd level, you can throw aside all concern for defense to attack with fierce desperation. When you make your first attack on your turn, you can decide to attack recklessly. Doing so gives you advantage on melee weapon attack rolls using Strength during this turn, but attack rolls against you have advantage until your next turn.
Danger Sense			KEY:Barbarian ~ Danger Sense			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.48	DESC:At 2nd level, you gain an uncanny sense of when things nearby aren't as they should be, giving you an edge when you dodge away from danger. You have advantage on Dexterity saving throws against effects that you can see, such as traps and spells. To gain this benefit, you can't be blinded, deafened, or incapacitated.
Primal Path				KEY:Barbarian ~ Primal Path			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.48	DESC:At 3rd level, you choose a path that shapes the nature of your rage. Choose the Path of the Berserker or the Path of the Totem Warrior, both detailed at the end of the class description. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th, 10th, and 14th levels.	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Barbarian Primal Path|1
Ability Score Improvement	KEY:Barbarian ~ Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.49	DESC:When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can't increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.
Extra Attack			KEY:Barbarian ~ Extra Attack			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.49	DESC:Beginning at 5th level, you can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.
Fast Movement			KEY:Barbarian ~ Fast Movement			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.49	DESC:Starting at 5th level, your speed increases by 10 feet while you aren't wearing heavy armor.
Feral Instinct			KEY:Barbarian ~ Feral Instinct		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.49	DESC:By 7th level, your instincts are so honed that you have advantage on initiative rolls. Additionally, if you are surprised at the beginning of combat and aren't incapacitated, you can act normally on your first turn, but only if you enter your rage before doing anything else on that turn.
Brutal Critical			KEY:Barbarian ~ Brutal Critical		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.49	DESC:Beginning at 9th level, you can roll one additional weapon damage die when determining the extra damage for a critical hit with a melee attack. This increases to two additional dice at 13th level and three additional dice at 17th level.
Relentless Rage			KEY:Barbarian ~ Relentless Rage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.49	DESC:Starting at 11th level, your rage can keep you fighting despite grievous w ounds. If you drop to 0 hit points while you're raging and don't die outright, you can make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw. If you succeed, you drop to 1 hit point instead. Each time you use this feature after the first, the DC increases by 5. When you finish a short or long rest, the DC resets to 10.
Persistent Rage			KEY:Barbarian ~ Persistent Rage		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.49	DESC:Beginning at 15th level, your rage is so fierce that it ends early only if you fall unconscious or if you choose to end it.
Indomitable Might			KEY:Barbarian ~ Indomitable Might		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.49	DESC:Beginning at 18th level, if your total for a Strength check is less than your Strength score, you can use that score in place of the total.
Primal Champion			KEY:Barbarian ~ Primal Champion		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.ClassAbility.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.49	DESC:At 20th level, you embody the power of the wilds. Your Strength and Constitution scores increase by 4. Your maximum for those scores is now 24.

# Primal Paths
Path of the Berserker	KEY:Primal Path ~ Path of the Berserker		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Primal Path.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:For some barbarians, rage is a means to an end-—that end being violence. The Path of the Berserker is a path of untrammeled fury, slick with blood. As you enter the berserker's rage, you thrill in the chaos of battle, heedless of your own health or well-being.
#
Frenzy			KEY:Path of the Berserker ~ Frenzy				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Berserker.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Starting when you choose this path at 3rd level, you can go into a frenzy when you rage. If you do so, for the duration of your rage you can make a single melee weapon attack as a bonus action on each of your turns after this one. When your rage ends, you suffer one level of exhaustion (as described in appendix A).
Mindless Rage		KEY:Path of the Berserker ~ Mindless Rage			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Berserker.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Beginning at 6th level, you can't be charmed or frightened while raging. If you are charmed or frightened when you enter your rage, the effect is suspended for the duration of the rage.
Intimidating Presence	KEY:Path of the Berserker ~ Intimidating Presence	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Berserker.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Beginning at 10th level, you can use your action to frighten someone with your menacing presence. When you do so, choose one creature that you can see within 30 feet of you. If the creature can see or hear you, it must succeed on a W isdom saving throw (DC equal to 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier) or be frightened of you until the end of your next turn. On subsequent turns, you can use your action to extend the duration of this effect on the frightened creature until the end of your next turn. This effect ends if the creature ends its turn out of line of sight or more than 60 feet away from you. If the creature succeeds on its saving throw, you can't use this feature on that creature again for 24 hours.
Retaliation			KEY:Path of the Berserker ~ Retaliation			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Berserker.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Starting at 14th level, when you take damage from a creature that is within 5 feet of you. you can use your reaction to make a melee weapon attack against that creature.

Path of the Totem Warrior	KEY:Primal Path ~ Path of the Totem Warrior		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Primal Path.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:The Path of the Totem Warrior is a spiritual journey, as the barbarian accepts a spirit animal as guide, protector, and inspiration. In battle, your totem spirit fills you with supernatural might, adding magical fuel to your barbarian rage. Most barbarian tribes consider a totem animal to be kin to a particular clan. In such cases, it is unusual for an individual to have more than one totem animal spirit, though exceptions exist.
#
Spirit Seeker		KEY:Path of the Totem Warrior ~ Spirit Seeker				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Totem Warrior.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Yours is a path that seeks attunement with the natural world, giving you a kinship with beasts. At 3rd level when you adopt this path, you gain the ability to cast the beast sense and speak with animals spells, but only as rituals, as described in chapter 10.
Totem Spirit		KEY:Path of the Totem Warrior ~ Totem Spirit				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Totem Warrior.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 3rd level, when you adopt this path, you choose a totem spirit and gain its feature. You must make or acquire a physical totem object- an amulet or similar adornment—that incorporates fur or feathers, claws, teeth, or b ones of the totem animal. At your option, you also gain minor physical attributes that are reminiscent of your totem spirit. For example, if you have a bear totem spirit, you might be unusually hairy and thickskinned, or if your totem is the eagle, your eyes turn bright yellow. Your totem animal might be an animal related to those listed here but more appropriate to your homeland. For example, you could choose a hawk or vulture in place of an eagle.	DESC: Bear. While raging, you have resistance to all damage except psychic damage. The spirit of the bear makes you tough enough to stand up to any punishment.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Totem Spirit Choice ~ Bear	DESC: Eagle. While you're raging and aren't wearing heavy armor, other creatures have disadvantage on opportunity attack rolls against you, and you can use the Dash action as a bonus action on your turn. The spirit of the eagle makes you into a predator w ho can weave through the fray with ease.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Totem Spirit Choice ~ Eagle	DESC: Wolf. While you're raging, your friends have advantage on melee attack rolls against any creature within 5 feet of you that is hostile to you. The spirit of the wolf makes you a leader of hunters.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Totem Spirit Choice ~ Wolf		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Totem Spirit Choice|1
Aspect of the Beast	KEY:Path of the Totem Warrior ~ Aspect of the Beast			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Totem Warrior.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 6th level, you gain a magical benefit based on the totem animal of your choice. You can choose the same animal you selected at 3rd level or a different one.	DESC: Bear. You gain the might of a bear. Your carrying capacity (including maximum load and maximum lift) is doubled, and you have advantage on Strength checks made to push, pull, lift, or break objects.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Aspect of the Beast Choice ~ Bear	DESC: Eagle. You gain the eyesight of an eagle. You can see up to 1 mile away with no difficulty, able to discern even fine details as though looking at something no more than 100 feet away from you. Additionally, dim light doesn't impose disadvantage on your Wisdom (Perception) checks.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Aspect of the Beast Choice ~ Eagle	DESC: Wolf. You gain the hunting sensibilities of a wolf. You can track other creatures while traveling at a fast pace, and you can move stealthily while traveling at a normal pace (see chapter 8 for rules on travel pace).|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Aspect of the Beast Choice ~ Wolf		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Aspect of the Beast Choice|1
Spirit Walker		KEY:Path of the Totem Warrior ~ Spirit Walker				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Totem Warrior.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 10th level, you can cast the commune with nature spell, but only as a ritual. When you do so, a spiritual version of one of the animals you chose for Totem Spirit or Aspect of the Beast appears to you to convey the information you seek.
Totemic Attunement	KEY:Path of the Totem Warrior ~ Totemic Attunement			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Path of the Totem Warrior.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 14th level, you gain a magical benefit based on a totem animal of your choice. You can choose the same animal you selected previously or a different one.	DESC: Bear. While you're raging, any creature within 5 feet of you that's hostile to you has disadvantage on attack rolls against targets other than you or another character with this feature. An enemy is immune to this effect if it can't see or hear you or if it can't be frightened.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Totemic Attunement ~ Bear	DESC: Eagle. While raging, you have a flying speed equal to your current walking speed. This benefit works only in short bursts; you fall if you end your turn in the air and nothing else is holding you aloft.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Totemic Attunement ~ Eagle	DESC: Wolf. While you're raging, you can use a bonus action on your turn to knock a Large or smaller creature prone when you hit it with melee w eapon attack.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Totemic Attunement ~ Wolf		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Totemic Attunement|1

# Totem Spirit Choice
Bear	KEY:Totem Spirit Choice ~ Bear	TYPE:Path of the Totem Warrior Totem Spirit Choice	CATEGORY:Internal	DESC: Bear. While raging, you have resistance to all damage except psychic damage. The spirit of the bear makes you tough enough to stand up to any punishment.
Eagle	KEY:Totem Spirit Choice ~ Eagle	TYPE:Path of the Totem Warrior Totem Spirit Choice	CATEGORY:Internal	DESC: Eagle. While you're raging and aren't wearing heavy armor, other creatures have disadvantage on opportunity attack rolls against you, and you can use the Dash action as a bonus action on your turn. The spirit of the eagle makes you into a predator w ho can weave through the fray with ease.
Wolf	KEY:Totem Spirit Choice ~ Wolf	TYPE:Path of the Totem Warrior Totem Spirit Choice	CATEGORY:Internal	DESC: Wolf. While you're raging, your friends have advantage on melee attack rolls against any creature within 5 feet of you that is hostile to you. The spirit of the wolf makes you a leader of hunters.

# Aspect of the Beast Choice
Bear	KEY:Aspect of the Beast Choice ~ Bear	TYPE:Path of the Totem Warrior Aspect of the Beast Choice	CATEGORY:Internal	DESC: Bear. You gain the might of a bear. Your carrying capacity (including maximum load and maximum lift) is doubled, and you have advantage on Strength checks made to push, pull, lift, or break objects.
Eagle	KEY:Aspect of the Beast Choice ~ Eagle	TYPE:Path of the Totem Warrior Aspect of the Beast Choice	CATEGORY:Internal	DESC: Eagle. You gain the eyesight of an eagle. You can see up to 1 mile away with no difficulty, able to discern even fine details as though looking at something no more than 100 feet away from you. Additionally, dim light doesn't impose disadvantage on your Wisdom (Perception) checks.
Wolf	KEY:Aspect of the Beast Choice ~ Wolf	TYPE:Path of the Totem Warrior Aspect of the Beast Choice	CATEGORY:Internal	DESC: Wolf. You gain the hunting sensibilities of a wolf. You can track other creatures while traveling at a fast pace, and you can move stealthily while traveling at a normal pace (see chapter 8 for rules on travel pace).

# Totemic Attunement
Bear	KEY:Totemic Attunement ~ Bear		TYPE:Path of the Totem Warrior Totemic Attunement	CATEGORY:Internal	DESC: Bear. While you're raging, any creature within 5 feet of you that's hostile to you has disadvantage on attack rolls against targets other than you or another character with this feature. An enemy is immune to this effect if it can't see or hear you or if it can't be frightened.
Eagle	KEY:Totemic Attunement ~ Eagle	TYPE:Path of the Totem Warrior Totemic Attunement	CATEGORY:Internal	DESC: Eagle. While raging, you have a flying speed equal to your current walking speed. This benefit works only in short bursts; you fall if you end your turn in the air and nothing else is holding you aloft.
Wolf	KEY:Totemic Attunement ~ Wolf		TYPE:Path of the Totem Warrior Totemic Attunement	CATEGORY:Internal	DESC: Wolf. While you're raging, you can use a bonus action on your turn to knock a Large or smaller creature prone when you hit it with melee w eapon attack.


###Block: Bard	
Spellcasting			KEY:Bard ~ Spellcasting				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.52	DESC:You have learned to untangle and reshape the fabric of reality in harmony with your wishes and music. Your spells are part of your vast repertoire, magic that you can tune to different situations. See chapter 10 for the general rules of spellcasting and chapter 11 for the bard spell list.	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Bard Spell Known Selection|BardLVL-2|PRECLASS:1,Bard=3	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Bard Spell Known Replacement|BardLVL-2|PRECLASS:1,Bard=3	DEFINE:BardRemoveSpellLVL|0	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Bard Remove Spell Known|BardRemoveSpellLVL
Cantrips				KEY:Bard ~ Cantrips				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.52	DESC:You know two cantrips of your choice from the bard spell list. You learn additional bard cantrips of your choice at higher levels, as shown in the Cantrips Known column of the Bard table.
Bardic Inspiration		KEY:Bard ~ Bardic Inspiration			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.53	DESC:You can inspire others through stirring w ords or music. To do so, you use a bonus action on your turn to choose one creature other than yourself within 60 feet of you who can hear you. That creature gains one Bardic Inspiration die, a d6. Once within the next 10 minutes, the creature can roll the die and add the number rolled to one ability check, attack roll, or saving throw it makes. The creature can wait until after it rolls the d20 before deciding to use the Bardic Inspiration die, but must decide before the DM says whether the roll succeeds or fails. Once the Bardic Inspiration die is rolled, it is lost. A creature can have only one Bardic Inspiration die at a time. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (a minimum of once). You regain any expended uses when you finish a long rest. Your Bardic Inspiration die changes when you reach certain levels in this class. The die becomes a d8 at 5th level, a d 10 at 10th level, and a d l2 at 15th level.
Jack of All Trades		KEY:Bard ~ Jack of All Trades			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.54	DESC:Starting at 2nd level, you can add half your proficiency bonus, rounded down, to any ability check you make that doesn't already include your proficiency bonus.
Song of Rest			KEY:Bard ~ Song of Rest				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.54	DESC:Beginning at 2nd level, you can use soothing music or oration to help revitalize your wounded allies during a short rest. If you or any friendly creatures w ho can hear your performance regain hit points at the end of the short rest, each of those creatures regains an extra 1d6 hit points. The extra hit points increase when you reach certain levels in this class: to 1d8 at 9th level, to 1d 10 at 13th level, and to 1d 12 at 17th level.
Bard College			KEY:Bard ~ Bard College				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.54	DESC:At 3rd level, you delve into the advanced techniques of a bard college of your choice: the College of Lore or the College of Valor, both detailed at the end of the class description. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th and 14th level.	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Bard College|1
Expertise				KEY:Bard ~ Expertise				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.54	DESC:At 3rd level, choose two of your skill proficiencies. Your proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses either of the chosen proficiencies. At 10th level, you can choose another two skill proficiencies to gain this benefit.
Ability Score Improvement	KEY:Bard ~ Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.54	DESC:When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability s cores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can't increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.
Font of Inspiration		KEY:Bard ~ Font of Inspiration		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.54	DESC:Beginning when you reach 5th level, you regain all of your expended uses of Bardic Inspiration when you finish a short or long rest.
Countercharm			KEY:Bard ~ Countercharm				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.54	DESC:At 6th level, you gain the ability to use musical notes or words of power to disrupt mind-influencing effects. As an action, you can start a performance that lasts until the end of your next turn. During that time, you and any friendly creatures within 30 feet of you have advantage on saving throws against being frightened or charmed. A creature must be able to hear you to gain this benefit. The performance ends early if you are incapacitated or silenced or if you voluntarily end it (no action required).
Magical Secrets			KEY:Bard ~ Magical Secrets			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.54	DESC:By 10th level, you have plundered magical knowledge from a w ide spectrum of disciplines. Choose two spells from any class, including this one. A spell you choose must be of a level you can cast, as shown on the Bard table, or a cantrip. The chosen spells count as bard spells for you and are included in the number in the Spells Known column of the Bard table. You learn two additional spells from any class at 14th level and again at 18th level.
Superior Inspiration		KEY:Bard ~ Superior Inspiration		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.54	DESC:At 20th level, when you roll initiative and have no uses of Bardic Inspiration left, you regain one use.

# Bard Colleges
College of Lore			KEY:Bard College ~ College of Lore				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Bard College.SpecialQuality		SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Bards of the College of Lore know something about most things, collecting bits of knowledge from sources as diverse as scholarly tomes and peasant tales. Whether singing folk ballads in taverns or elaborate compositions in royal courts, these bards use their gifts to hold audiences spellbound. When the applause dies down, the audience members might find themselves questioning everything they held to be true, from their faith in the priesthood of the local temple to their loyalty to the king. The loyalty of these bards lies in the pursuit of beauty and truth, not in fealty to a monarch or following the tenets of a deity. A noble who keeps such a bard as a herald or advisor knows that the bard w ould rather be honest than politic. The college's members gather in libraries and sometimes in actual colleges, complete with classrooms and dormitories, to share their lore with one another. They also meet at festivals or affairs of state, where they can expose corruption, unravel lies, and poke fun at selfimportant figures of authority.	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of Lore ~ Bonus Proficiencies|PRECLASS:1,Bard=3	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of Lore ~ Cutting Words|PRECLASS:1,Bard=3	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of Lore ~ Additional Magical Secrets|PRECLASS:1,Bard=6	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of Lore ~ Peerless Skill|PRECLASS:1,Bard=14			
#
Bonus Proficiencies		KEY:College of Lore ~ Bonus Proficiencies			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.College of Lore.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:When you join the College of Lore at 3rd level, you gain proficiency with three skills of your choice.
Cutting Words			KEY:College of Lore ~ Cutting Words				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.College of Lore.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Also at 3rd level, you learn how to use your wit to distract, confuse, and otherwise sap the confidence and competence of others. When a creature that you can see within 60 feet of you makes an attack roll, an ability check, or a damage roll, you can use your reaction to expend one of your uses of Bardic Inspiration, rolling a Bardic Inspiration die and subtracting the number rolled from the creature's roll. You can choose to use this feature after the creature makes its roll, but before the DM determines whether the attack roll or ability check succeeds or fails, or before the creature deals its damage. The creature is immune if it can't hear you or if it's immune to being charmed.
Additional Magical Secrets	KEY:College of Lore ~ Additional Magical Secrets	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.College of Lore.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 6th level, you learn two spells of your choice from any class. A spell you choose must be of a level you can cast, as shown on the Bard table, or a cantrip. The chosen spells count as bard spells for you but don't count against the number of bard spells you know.
Peerless Skill			KEY:College of Lore ~ Peerless Skill			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.College of Lore.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Starting at 14th level, when you make an ability check, you can expend one use of Bardic Inspiration. Roll a Bardic Inspiration die and add the number rolled to your ability check. You can choose to do so after you roil the die for the ability check, but before the DM tells you whether you succeed or fail.

College of Valor		KEY:Bard College ~ College of Valor			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Bard College.SpecialQuality		SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Bards of the College of Valor are daring skalds whose tales keep alive the memory of the great heroes of the past, and thereby inspire a new generation of heroes. These bards gather in mead halls or around great bonfires to sing the deeds of the mighty, both past and present. They travel the land to witness great events firsthand and to ensure that the memory of those events doesn't pass from the world. With their songs, they inspire others to reach the same heights of accomplishment as the heroes of old.	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of Valor ~ Bonus Proficiencies|PRECLASS:1,Bard=3	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of Valor ~ Combat Inspiration|PRECLASS:1,Bard=3	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of Valor ~ Extra Attack|PRECLASS:1,Bard=6	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of Valor ~ Battle Magic|PRECLASS:1,Bard=14			
#
Bonus Proficiencies	KEY:College of Valor ~ Bonus Proficiencies	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.College of Valor.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:When you join the College of Valor at 3rd level, you gain proficiency with medium armor, shields, and martial weapons.
Combat Inspiration	KEY:College of Valor ~ Combat Inspiration		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.College of Valor.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Also at 3rd level, you learn to inspire others in battle. A creature that has a Bardic Inspiration die from you can roll that die and add the number rolled to a weapon damage roll it just made. Alternatively, when an attack roll is made against the creature, it can use its reaction to roll the Bardic Inspiration die and add the number rolled to its AC against that attack, after seeing the roll but before knowing whether it hits or misses.
Extra Attack		KEY:College of Valor ~ Extra Attack			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.College of Valor.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Starting at 6th level, you can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.
Battle Magic		KEY:College of Valor ~ Battle Magic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.College of Valor.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 14th level, you have mastered the art of weaving spellcasting and weapon use into a single harmonious act. When you use your action to cast a bard spell, you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action.

